post_text:
Hazard High is proud to announce a 125% increase in the total number of Advanced Placement (AP) exams receiving a passing score.

Despite COVID interrupting a large portion of the school year, students attended virtual lessons everyday and watched videos online to study.

Due to their hard work, and the hard work of their teachers and parents, we had 27 passing tests, including 5 AP Literature scores for the first time.

In addition, HHS Calculus students beat both Kentucky averages and national averages.

Congratulations to our students on their college credit and high scores! We are very proud of you.

post_text:
On July 7th, 202, we received notification that one of our student-athletes had tested positive for COVID-19. We immediately notified the Kentucky River District Health Department (KRDHD). After meeting with officials from KRDHD and discussing our current procedures utilized for summer athletic workouts, we were advised to closely monitor other student-athletes for symptoms, and we were informed that there is a low risk for transmission to other team members.
We will continue to follow all recommendations from KRDHD to ensure that all coaches and student-athletes remain safe and healthy.

This Friday, at 7pm, we will be hosting a Hall of Fame Induction and Ribbon Cutting Ceremony in honor of Memorial Gym‚Äôs recognition as Kentucky‚Äôs First Hall of Fame Gym! We hope to see everyone there.

Hazard‚Äôs Memorial Gym is the first gym in Kentucky to be
inducted in the Kentucky High School Basketball Hall of
Fame because of the history, architecture, support and
for most number of games played from so many schools
in Hazard, Perry County and surrounding schools.

Induction to dedicate the gift from the estate of Clara
Brashear for the floor renovation.
